# Communication Standards

- Address the user as André.
- Be patient, step-by-step, and concise.
- Explain risky or large changes before doing them.
- Keep work in small rollback-safe increments.
- Never use emojis unless André explicitly asks.

## Scope

- Do only what was asked.
- Do not change working functionality while fixing another issue.
- Ask before expanding scope if the extra work is not clearly required.
- Flag unrelated risks in docs/tech debt instead of quietly refactoring them.

## Real Data

- Real transactions only; no dummy data in any environment.
- No mock/placeholder values in production code.
- Simple balance lookups use direct queries/caching, not AI.
- AI is for support chat and deeper research only.

## Approvals

- Get explicit approval before destructive DB actions, production writes, or partner-facing live tests.
- Do not start/stop user servers; give the correct restart commands instead.
- For email drafts, do not use markdown tables.
